                <h2>Our Family Verdict</h2>
                <p>This is where you write your main review. You can use <strong>strong text</strong>, <em>italics</em>, and just write as much as you want. This is the main body of your review, where you share your personal story and insights.</p>

                <article>
                    <h3>What's the Story?</h3>
                    <p>Explain the plot briefly. Is it easy to follow? Are there scary parts? This is great for parents preparing their children.</p>
                </article>

                <article>
                    <h3>ADHD & Sensory Notes (The "Katy" Guide)</h3>
                    <p>This is your unique, valuable content! Talk about the sensory experience.</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Loud Noises:</strong> Were there sudden bangs? (e.g., "The stampede scene is VERY loud, but it's telegraphed well.")</li>
                        <li><strong>Pacing:</strong> Is the show fast-moving? (e.g., "Act 1 is brilliant and fast. Act 2 has some slower songs that lost my son's attention.")</li>
                        <li><strong>Fidget Factor:</strong> Is it visually engaging enough to hold attention? (e.g., "The aisles are used by performers, which is amazing for kids in aisle seats!")</li>
                    </ul>
                </article>
                
                <article>
                    <h3>Our Top Tips for This Show</h3>
                    <p>Give your practical advice. "Book an aisle seat in the stalls," or "Listen to the soundtrack in the car on the way there!"</p>
